<h2 id="who-its-for">👥 Who This Software Is For</h2>

**Best fit for personal training software:**

- **Independent trainers with 20+ clients** — The break-even point where efficiency gains justify costs
- **Gym owners adding PT revenue streams** — Centralized management across multiple trainers
- **Online coaches scaling beyond 1:1** — Deliver programming to more clients without proportional time increase
- **Hybrid fitness businesses** — Combine in-person sessions with app-based programming
- **Franchise operators** — Standardize training delivery across locations

**Not ideal for:**

- **Trainers with fewer than 10 clients** — Spreadsheets and WhatsApp work fine at this scale
- **Group fitness-only operations** — Class booking software is a different category
- **Operators who won't enforce adoption** — Software only works if trainers actually use it

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> When rolling out new software to an existing trainer team, start with your highest-performing trainer, not your most tech-savvy one. Success stories from top performers drive adoption faster than IT enthusiasm.
</div>

